context: Definitions of "<b6_0>Southeast Asia<b6_0/>" vary, but most definitions include the area represented by the countries (sovereign states and dependent territories) listed below. All of the states except for <a3_0>East Timor<a3_0/> are members of <b4_0>the <a1_0>Association of Southeast Asian Nations<b4_0/><a1_0/> (ASEAN). The area, together with part of South Asia, was widely known as the <b5_0>East Indies<b5_0/> or simply the Indies until the 20th century. <a2_0><b7_0><b8_0>Christmas Island and the Cocos<b8_0/><b7_0/> (Keeling) Islands<a2_0/>[citation needed] are considered part of Southeast Asia though they are governed by Australia.[citation needed] Sovereignty issues exist over some territories in the South China Sea. <a0_0>Papua New Guinea<a0_0/> has stated that it might join ASEAN, and is currently an observer.
